====Usage notes====
The scientific definition of what organisms should be considered plants changed dramatically during the 20th century with the rise of advanced micrscopy techniques and DNA sequencing.  Many textbooks do not reflect the most current thinking on classification.  Bacteria, algae, and fungi are no longer considered plants by botanists, though they are still called plants by ecologists because of their shared ability to carry out photosynthesis.

